Keith J. Allman  Chief Executive Officer, President and Director, Masco CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships54$9,765,728As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Keith J. Allman has been the Chief Executive Officer and President at Masco Corporation since February 14, 2014. Mr. Allman served as the Group President of Masco Corporation from November 22, 2011 to February 14, 2014 and was responsible for Masco's Plumbing and North American Cabinet businesses. He was responsible for Brasstech, Delta Faucet Company, Hansgrohe, Liberty Hardware, Masco Bath, Masco Canada and Mirolin Industries Corporation. Mr. Allman has experience ... in the automotive and home building industries. He served as the President of Masco Corporation Of Indiana (also known as Delta Faucet Company) from April 9, 2007 to 2011. He joined Masco in 1998 as Vice President of Manufacturing at the Masco 's cabinet maker Merillat Industries. He served as an Executive Vice President of Operations at Masco's Builder Cabinet Group. Prior to joining Masco, he spent 13 years with General Motors in a variety of manufacturing, engineering and quality positions. Following his career at GM, he worked in the automotive tier one supply base in a number of senior leadership positions. He serves as a Member of Supervisory Board at Hansgrohe SE. He has been an Independent Director of Oshkosh Corporation since September 15, 2015. He has been a Director of Masco Corporation since February 14, 2014. Mr. Allman received his Bachelor of Science degree in Mechanical Engineering from General Motors Institute (now Kettering University) and a Master of Business Administration degree from the Stephen M. Ross School of Business at the University of Michigan.Read Full Background




