Keith J. Allman 

		
		President and CEO, 

	
		 Masco Corporation 	

 
Last Updated: 04/03/2017 



Executive Summary
Keith Allman serves as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Masco Corporation, one of the world’s leading manufacturers of home improvement and building products.  Allman previously was a Masco Group President. He joined the Company 1998 as Vice President of Manufacturing for cabinet maker Merillat Industries. In 200 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Allman is married. He and his wife, Miria, have two children.
Allman was honored with the Outstanding Achievement award at one of Kettering's Bulldog Alumni Reunion weekend. 
Current Focus

Company Overview: Headquartered in Taylor, Michigan, Masco Corporation is a global leader in the design, manufacture and distribution of branded home improvement and building products. Its portfolio of brands includes B 
Biographical Highlights

Born circa 1963.
Allman earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Mechanical Engineering from General Motors Institute (Kettering University) in 1985. 
Other Boards and Organizations

Member, Alpha Tau Omega fraternity
Member, Supervisory Board, Hansgrohe SE  
 





